A
STATISTICAL
STUDY
OF
IONOSPHERIC
DRIFTS
MEASURED
BY
THE
RADIO
STAR
SCINTILLATION
TECHNIQUE
THE
METHOD
GIVES
THE
EW
COMPONENT
OF
THE
DRIFT
VELOCITY
THROUGHOUT
THE
DAY
THIS
COMPONENT
IS
COMMONLY
FOUND
TO
REVERSE
SUDDENLY
NEAR
BUT
THE
COMPLEMENTARY
REVERSAL
OCCURS
AT
A
LESS
DEFINITE
TIME
DURING
THE
FOLLOWING
DAY
